revisions.description: Local/remote IP address, mask, gateway OIDs added
No modem distortion data is available on Integra-W
No carrier offset and modem temp. data are available on Integra-W
Public Release 1.04. Radio PLL status, free physical memory, CPU idle objects added
Public Release 1.03. Added OIDs for modem signal quality and distortion

integraWradioTxMute.name: integraWradioTxMute
integraWradioTxMute.description: Status of 'Tx mute' 1 - Tx is muted, 2 - Tx is not muted. 3 - Status information unavailable

integraWradioTxMuteDuration.name: integraWradioTxMuteDuration
integraWradioTxMuteDuration.description: Time remaning for Tx to be muted in seconds. To turn mute on send number of seconds between 10 and MAX. To turn mute off send 0. GET will retrieve remaining duration for mute or 0 if Tx mute is turned off.

integraWradioRangeEntry.name: integraWradioRangeEntry
integraWradioRangeEntry.description: An entry containing network physical port status info.

integraWradioRangeEntryIndex.name: integraWradioRangeEntryIndex
integraWradioRangeEntryIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each range entry. Starts with 1 and is equal to a number of all range parameters.

integraWradioRangeTxPower.name: integraWradioRangeTxPower
integraWradioRangeTxPower.description: Output power ranges for integraWradio transmitter

integraWmodemAcquireStatus.name: integraWmodemAcquireStatus
integraWmodemAcquireStatus.description: This is the current status of modem data acquire when queried modem status. For detailed info use modemAcquireLastStatusDetails.

integraWmodemMse.name: integraWmodemMse
integraWmodemMse.description: Current MSE value (floating point value multiplied by 10)

integraWmodemFecLoad.name: integraWmodemFecLoad
integraWmodemFecLoad.description: Decoder stress or FEC load value (floating point in textual representation)

integraWmodemRxCapacity.name: integraWmodemRxCapacity
integraWmodemRxCapacity.description: Rx ethernet capacity in kilobits per second

integraWmodemTxCapacity.name: integraWmodemTxCapacity
integraWmodemTxCapacity.description: Tx ethernet capacity in kilobits per second

integraWsysLicenseExpire.name: integraWsysLicenseExpire
integraWsysLicenseExpire.description: License expires after number of seconds. In the case of -1, check licenseGenStatus status

integraWifPortEntry.name: integraWifPortEntry
integraWifPortEntry.description: An entry containing network physical port status info.

integraWifPortStatIndex.name: integraWifPortStatIndex
integraWifPortStatIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each physical network interface. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1.

integraWifPortStatDescr.name: integraWifPortStatDescr
integraWifPortStatDescr.description: Physical network interface description. LAN1 is electrical, LAN2 and LAN3 are SFP and WAN is radio port.

integraWifPortType.name: integraWifPortType
integraWifPortType.description: The type of interface, distinguished according to the physical/link protocol(s) immediately `below' the network layer in the protocol stack.

integraWifPortMtu.name: integraWifPortMtu
integraWifPortMtu.description: Maximum transmission unit value in bytes.

integraWifPortSpeed.name: integraWifPortSpeed
integraWifPortSpeed.description: Link speed in bits per second.

integraWifPortPhysAddress.name: integraWifPortPhysAddress
integraWifPortPhysAddress.description: The interface's address at the protocol layer immediately `below' the network layer in the protocol stack. For interfaces which do not have such an address (e.g., a serial line), this object should contain an octet string of zero length.

integraWifPortAdminStatus.name: integraWifPortAdminStatus
integraWifPortAdminStatus.description: Desired state of network interfaces. Interfaces can be enabled(1), disabled(2), unknown(3) (no info received).

integraWifPortOperStatus.name: integraWifPortOperStatus
integraWifPortOperStatus.description: Actual state of interfaces. Link can be up(1), down(2) or in unknown(3) state.

integraWifPortLastChange.name: integraWifPortLastChange
integraWifPortLastChange.description: This parameter value is always 0 at the moment.

integraWifPortAutoneg.name: integraWifPortAutoneg
integraWifPortAutoneg.description: Auto-negotiation status. Unknown means no info was received.

integraWifPortSyncEthActive.name: integraWifPortSyncEthActive
integraWifPortSyncEthActive.description: Synchronous Ethernet status. Can be active(1) or inactive(0).

integraWifPortStcEntry.name: integraWifPortStcEntry
integraWifPortStcEntry.description: An entry containing network physical port statistics counter data.

integraWifPortStcIndex.name: integraWifPortStcIndex
integraWifPortStcIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each physical network interface. It is recommended that values are assigned contiguously starting from 1.

integraWifPortStcDescr.name: integraWifPortStcDescr
integraWifPortStcDescr.description: Physical network interface description. LAN1 is electrical, LAN2 and LAN3 are SFP, WAN is radio port and MNG is internal management interface.

integraWexecuteConfig.name: integraWexecuteConfig
integraWexecuteConfig.description: This object can only be set to 1. It initiates new running configuration applying using values, that have been set before. Setting it when no new changes are available will do nothing and return an error. GET will return 0 if there were no errors, while executing configuration or will return a bitmask, that shows which SET requests have failed. Those failed requests will be shown bit wise from LSB as follows: BIT0 radioTxMuteDuration BIT1 radioTxFrequency BIT2 radioTxPower

integraWneedStore.name: integraWneedStore
integraWneedStore.description: This object shows if there is unsaved, but executed (running) configuration. Unsaved changes will be lost after device reboot. Unsaved entities are shown bit wise, starting from LSB as follows: BIT0 Aggregation BIT1 Event log BIT2 Modem BIT3 Network BIT4 Performance BIT5 Radio BIT6 SNMP BIT7 Synchronous Ethernet BIT8 System

integraWstoreConfig.name: integraWstoreConfig
integraWstoreConfig.description: This object can only be set to 1. It initiates saving of running configuration. It will only work if there are unsaved, but executed (running) changes (configuration). Setting it when no new running configuration is available will do nothing and return an error.

integraWnetCfgIPgateway.name: integraWnetCfgIPgateway
integraWnetCfgIPgateway.description: IP gateway Send '0' or '255.255.255.255' to clear.

integraWCompliance.name: integraWCompliance
integraWCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP engine which implements the SAF Tehnika Integra-W device.

integraWEthernetGeneralGroup.name: integraWEthernetGeneralGroup
integraWEthernetGeneralGroup.description: A collection to objects, providing info applicable to all network interfaces.

integraWEthernetMiiPortGroup.name: integraWEthernetMiiPortGroup
integraWEthernetMiiPortGroup.description: A collection of objects, providing info applicable only to MII group interfaces.
